headline: Is UPS a Bargain After Outsourcing Its Weather Forecasting to Cut Costs in 2025?
summary: If you’re puzzling over what to do with United Parcel Service stock right now, you’re not alone. The shipping giant’s shares closed at $87.44 recently, and investors have been on quite a ride. Over the past week, the price dipped by 1.6%, barely shifted up 0.3% over the month, and remains deep in the red year-to-date with a 29.4% drop. The one-year and three-year changes are hardly better, sitting at -27.7% and -48.5%, with the five-year return at -33.9%. With numbers like these, it’s fair to...
